 and through Shakespeare’s celebrated characters and actors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Shakespeare.2bisacsh  aBoy actors.  aChildhood Studies.  aEarly modern adolescence.  aEarly modern medicine.  aGender Studies.  aHumoral theory.  aRichard Burbage.  aShakespeare.  aShakespearean performance.  aSigns of puberty.1 aSparey, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2024 eBook-Packagez9783111332345oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616820740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526168207423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526168207/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2024